article.description: Luke Roh's career-high leads Colgate past Army 84-69
article.headline: Luke Roh's career-high leads Colgate past Army 84-69
article.linkText: Luke Roh's career-high leads Colgate past Army 84-69
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Luke Roh recorded his second career double-double with a career-high 25 points and 10 rebounds to help Colgate beat Army 84-69 on Wednesday night. The senior's previous best was 16 points. Roh made 8 of 10 first-half shots and his 18 points helped Colgate hold a 46-36 lead at the break. It was the Raiders' best offensive output in Patriot League play this season. Ethan Jacobs made 7 of 8 shots and finished with 19 points for Colgate (13-15, 10-5). Pat Moore added 11 points and Matt McMullen 10. A Moore 3-pointer gave Colgate its largest lead of the game at 18, 56-38. Army responded with a 12-3 run to pull within 59-50 midway through the half. Colgate's lead was cut to eight points with 2:47 left, but the Raiders outscored Army 11-4 down the stretch. Dylan Cox led Army (14-12, 5-10) with 17 points. Kevin Ferguson added 15.
